<br>
Her heart stopped beating, but as Nefer made her way down the hall to the bathroom, she pushed herself to her feet. Before Jerron got to the door she grabbed his arm, but from there she didn't really want to say a word. Carmen just, well, held on.<br>
<br>
Sadness washed over her, when Jerron refused to turn and look her in the eye. &quot;Jerron...&quot; Carmen said quietly, sadness and worry laced her silky voice. She didn't know where he went or even what he did, but he'd left like this at least twice now, maybe even three times. <br>
<br>
Carmen's storm-filled eyes, watched the back of his head, hoping he'd turn. She wanted to inquire what he was about to do, but maybe it was best just to let him go. <br>
<br>
Releasing Jerron's arm, Carmen stepped infront of him and got the door for him, but there was something, someone blocking the way...<br>
<br>
The heap on the ground, resembled a hybrid of cat and human, there was only one of those she knew... <br>
<br>
&quot;Oh my... God...&quot; Carmen muttered as she knelt beside him. She didn't want to touch him, because she was scared of hurting him. His shirt was ripped half-way to Sunday, and his ear was bleeding. Reaching out to touch his ear she pulled her finger back. Carmen really didn't want to touch a place that was injured. <br>
<br>
Scared violet eyes looked up to Jerron, as she placed a hand on Devin's back. The rise and fall motion of his back, indicated breathing, she was oh-so thankful for that. Was he awake though? &quot;Devin...&quot; Carmen called to him quietly, as she shook him lightly, trying to rouse him, &quot;Talk to me...&quot;<br>
<br>
