A wobbling ring of grey smoke slowly lifted towards the ceiling before expanding and disappearing. A cigarette hung between Nefertiti's middle and pointer finger as she lay sprawled out in the tub. Slowly she brought the filter to her lips and sucked in the sweet taste of tobacco. Her arm flopped back down over the side of the bathtub and the beads dangling from the leather strap on her arm clicked against the side of the porcelin. If there was one thing Nefertiti still found peace in it was laying in an unfilled tub. Smoke poured from her mouth as she exhailed. One thing about her still hadn't changed - her woredrobe. Baggy black canvas pants and tight black tanktops. And always, always that same leather strap on her arm with two dangling strings that held 7 various shades of blue beads at the ends. The lengths of the strings were different by an inch or two. Knotted, wavey brown locks fell around her face matted and stringy. Though she didn't smell it had probably been two or more days since she had showered. The past four nights had been spent drowning her many sorrows in bottle after bottle and last night everyone had had a good drowning. Finding comfort in another puff she lays her head back and lets her mind blank out. There was nothing left to think about and all that was left to do was finish off the last of her camel red.<br>
