</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/bfantasystoriesforum.showUserPublicProfile?gid=rillen@fantasystoriesforum>Rillen</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_redspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Weaver of Flames</span><br>  Posts: 292<br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/21/02 9:49 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/ffantasystoriesforumfrm7.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=13.topic&index=18>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: S'Just Life</span><hr size=1> OOC (I was on my way out, but then devin appeared at the doorstep.  He was kinda, err, um, REALLY beat up, so right now Jerron and Carmen are caring for him in Jerron's bedroom while Nefer's smokin in the empty tub.  K.  Now, just gonna do my whole thing to TRY and help you understand.  It's gonna be hard, the last rp had I think 12 pages...  If you don't think you should know the last story, then DON'T READ THIS.  Well, Derek(mindles) was an orphan, I think Mika(Paradise) was too.  Nefer had parents, but wasn't a fan of that whole thing, and became friends with those two.  Jash and Devin I'm unsure of, I know that Jash, Devin, Mika, Nefer, Jerron, and Derek were all friends of at a young age.  Derek was kinda the unspoken leader of us all, and one of the few people Jerron actually opened up to.  Derek was a dealer.  He sold drugs(crystals?), and was a casual user along with the rest (baring Jerron.)  Yaddayadda yada, they went to a club.  Derek met with a customer there, Carmen.  Carmen and Jash hook up and fly around the room, they both are hoverboarders.  Mika and Nefer have a heart to heart(as Nefer said...lesbianism? mebee, at the most, more than close friends.)  Jerron meets a girl, Lor(laurana.)  Somehow, I forget, their minds touch and they 'understand' eachother.  I don't know what I was thinking when I wrote it....Devin hooks up with his gal, a bounty hunter, Kali.  They see Shadow, Devin's old flame(Devins bi) and have a little spat.  A little bout erupts between everyone minus carmen, and the Keeters.  A group of weirdos with mentalists(people in control of the mind related abilities of the time ex. controlling simple machines created for such purpose, entering peoples minds, altering thoughts, stimulating parts of the brain, etc.) and brutes(really big muscly men.)  Jash, Derik, Nefer, Mika, and Devin, and maybe Kali escape in Derik's car, Jerron steals Shadows.  They go back.  lots of talk etc etc, keeter fights etc.  Then they need to kill shadow for some reason or another.  Jerron teleports everyone back to his house, minus Derek.  He enters Derek's mind where Derek kicks shadow's arse.  They see a sign, the octarine.  They leave, go back to Jerron's house.  Derek remembers the octarine.  Jerron-yellow, Carmen-blue money, Devin-purple sex, Nefer-green likability, Mika red fighting, Jash, I ferget, and Derek is the head of em all.  He's good at everything.  Jerron goes to see Lor and find her injured, takes her to the hospital.  She raves about someone named Sarah.  Oh, and Shadow is black, death.  With shadow dieing/dead, Derek is dying too.  Shadow dies, and Kali takes over as octarine of death.  Mika turns into a Lamia, sucks life force from people.  She kisses Jerron and hurts him alot.  Then she touches Nefer and nefer is fine, and Mika starts to feel better.  Jerron and Devin go to get some keeters to feed her energy.  They go back to find everyone gone.  They left a message, going to india or something.  Derek knows where 'sarah' is, and thats where it died, the rp that is.  Hope that helped to clear things up.  If you have the time, I'd suggest you go back and read it, but if you don't, don't worry.   <br>
Devin's injuries proved to be not much more serious than cosmetical.  While he had sustained hard blows to his body, the cuts were minimal, and what he needed most was rest.  Carmen had carefully blotted away the blood with rags, torn strips of an old t-shirt.  With clean rags, she bound his nude upper torso.  He looked so....fragile, innocent, lying there unconscious.  At least he's not gone, gone like the others.  Staring at his friend made him realize how pitiful life really was.  He no longer wanted to be near Dev, near this body who all of a sudden stood for all that had gone wrong in the last month.  &quot;Carmen....<br>
She turned to look at him, eyes so full of hope.  &quot;He's so beautiful there, isn't he.&quot;<br>
&quot;Um, I'm going to go check on Nefer, its been a while.  I think I'll go out, get some lunch for later.  I...I just need to clear my head.&quot;  Jerron didn't know what to do.  He used to be so sure of himself, always landing on his feet.  Only now, he was smack on his ass without anything to help him to his feet. <br>
&quot;I understand.&quot;  She nodded, knowing what it meant to not know what to do.  <br>
Muttering 'thanks', too quietly for her to hear, Jerron left his room.  Smoke was steadily rolling forth from the bathroom, slowly filling the bottom floor.  He knocked, but didn't wait for a reply as he turned the knob.  The sight was almost comical, but it wasn't enough for Jerron to laugh for the first time in the month.  His friend was spralled out in the empty tub with a cigarette hanging from her mouth, a glazed look on her face.  &quot;I'm going out hon, lunch.  Wouldja like to come with?&quot;        <br>
 <p>Ignis Summa Pugnabat, The fires shall cleanse the world.</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/bfantasystoriesforum.showUserPublicProfile?gid=dahnyella>Dahnyella</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_lightning.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Child of Mischief</span><br>  Posts: 89<br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/22/02 8:09 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/ffantasystoriesforumfrm7.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=13.topic&index=19>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://img.ranchoweb.com/images/nikkidee/dahny.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: S'Just Life</span><hr size=1> Carmen sat there, just watching Devin. He was alive. HE was still with them, she wasn't going to lose another one. His state wasn't as bad as it looked, once they got the blood cleaned away, there were only a few scratches and bruises. Carmen wished that was how emotional wounds were... That they only looked bad, that they didn't FEEL so bad. <br>
<br>
&quot;Um, I'm going to go check on Nefer, its been a while. I think I'll go out, get some lunch for later. I...I just need to clear my head,&quot; Jerron piped up from behind her. His voice was kind of, lost. Hell, they all felt lost, even Carmen, the only thing that kept her going was knowing she had to protect what she had left. Neferiti, Jerron, Devin. She wanted to keep them right by her and never let them go. When Carmen met their little group, she knew that right there was where she wanted to be. Through thick. Through thin. Then, 3 of them... slipped away. Dead? Alive? They didn't know, but they knew they were gone. From the moment the realization of their absence hit, Carmen knew she wasn't going to let it happen to the others... no, no, no. In a way she felt like she was the 'mother goose' of her remaining friends, but someone had to be.<br>
<br>
Carmen brushed away all of the images and thoughts clouding her mind, slowly she began nodding, she knew how Jerron felt, &quot;I understand.&quot; Her violet eyes turned up to him, pleading he be careful.<br>
<br>
As he turned and left the room, Carmen thought she heard him say, 'Thanks,' but she wasn't too sure. Wincing as the door came to close, she hoped Jerron's little outting returned some clarity.<br>
<br>
Glancing back to Devin, she sighed. It was a beautiful sight to see her friend alright. Though he kept muttering now and then, he was probably talking in his sleep. <br>
<br>
Forcing herself up, she bent over and kissed his forehead, &quot;You'll be fine by tomorrow, Devin,&quot; she told him, even though he wasn't awake.<br>
<br>
Slowly, Carmen made her way out of the room. As her hand closed around the knob...<br>
<br>
&quot;Nefer...&quot;<br>
<br>
Carmen looked over her shoulder at Devin, 'He must be sleep talking,' she thought. <br>
<br>
Sighing, she left the room, and went to the kitchen. Still on the table was her legal pad and pen, &quot;Damn it,&quot; Carmen muttered. She hadn't heard activity from the front door yet, so Jerron had to have still been in the apartment. &quot;Jerron,&quot; she called out just enough to lace through the apartment. Maybe he wouldn't mind picking up these few things? <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><br>
<!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:red;font-family:verdana;font-size:small;">&quot;Beware the storm, it holds a stength beyond the imagination.&quot;</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><br>
</div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/bfantasystoriesforum.showUserPublicProfile?gid=bellonakali>Bellona Kali</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://auction.2y.net/user/kanachan/jsk2.JPG" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Child of Hate</span><br>  Posts: 667<br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/22/02 12:25 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/ffantasystoriesforumfrm7.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=13.topic&index=20>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://auction.2y.net/user/kanachan/XMas_1.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: S'Just Life</span><hr size=1> Go out? That idea was sketchy. But Jerron, the sweetheart, had taken the time to come in here and ask. He probably wanted some company. Well, if he wanted her to go... she might as well. Wouldn't hurt nothin, right? Flicking her cigarette into the toilet, she listened for that tiny hiss as the cherry went out. She always liked hearing that. Pushing herself to her feet she took a step out of the tub and looked at Jerron. Always she had thought him to be the strongest out of all of them and greatly admired the power his mind once held... but as she stared deep into his eyes she saw he was fighting to keep his head above water just like the rest. His eyes held so little of what they once did... He was hurting. As much or even more than she was, only he hid it. He hid it so that no one else could see how bad it pained him to live like this. Tears stung behind her eye lids. She sucked in her breath, apparently she still had a few tears left in her... Before she had a chance to start sobbing she threw her arms around Jerron and held him close. Why did every second of every day have to be so agonizing? They stood there for a few minutes, unable and unwilling to let go. <br>
